law.catch_line: Federal acts relating to vocational rehabilitation.
law.text: This state accepts and agrees to comply with all the provisions of the Acts of Congress of the United States approved June 2, 1920 (41 Stat. 735) relating to vocational rehabilitation and all subsequent acts when such acts apply to joint state and federally funded vocational rehabilitation programs.
law.history: Amended 1994 Ky. Acts ch. 363, sec. 8, effective July 15, 1994. -- Repealed, reenacted, and amended as KRS 151B.200 by 1990 Ky. Acts ch. 470, sec. 39, effective July 1, 1990, which prevailed over the repeal and reenactment of KRS 163.160 by 1990 Ky. Acts ch. 476, Pt. V, sec. 597, effective July 13, 1990. -- Amended 1984 Ky. Acts ch. 316, sec. 5, effective July 13, 1984. -- Amended 1980 Ky. Acts ch. 266, sec. 1, effective July 15, 1980. -- Created 1956 Ky. Acts ch. 172, sec. 6, effective May 18, 1956.

metadata.lrc-note: (7/13/90). The Act amending this section prevails over the repeal and reenactment in House Bill 940, Acts ch. 476, pursuant to Section 653(1) of Acts ch. 476.
